Commentary Text: Tymal Mills to Padikkal, out Caught by Rohit!! That's an excellent over from Mills. He built pressure by keeping Buttler quiet and was rewarded with Padikkal's wicket. With this being the last ball of the powerplay, Padikkal wanted to make the most of it and perishes in the process. He backs away and steps down, but Mills shortens his length and rushes him on the cross-batted shot, the ball hits the splice and balloon straight up, Rohit settles under it near cover. Padikkal c Rohit b Tymal Mills 7(7) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Chahal to Daniel Sams, out Caught by Buttler!! Golden duck for Sams! Atrocious shot first up from the all-rounder, especially with just few more deliveries of spin left. Floated up by Chahal, tempts the big shot and Sams falls into the trap. What a catch it is from Buttler though! This mishit was in the air for a lifetime, he trekked back and timed his dive perfectly near the deep mid-wicket region. Took it effortlessly. RR's spin twins are spinning their team to a win here. Or so it seems for now. Daniel Sams c Buttler b Chahal 0(1)

Commentary Text: Chahal to Tim David, out Lbw!! Cracking leg break from Chahal and he's dealt a huge blow here! Proper classical spin bowling, lands this around leg stump, sharp leg break that also skids a tad and David is pinned on the crease unable to negotiate the turn. Don't think he expected so much turn either. Struck on the back pad and it looked a fair shout in real time. Given by the ump and David tried to test his luck with DRS. In the end, it was a very marginal call. Just about pitching in line of leg stump and just clipping the top of off stump. RR are starting to gain an advantage here. Tim David lbw b Chahal 1(3)

Commentary Text: Boult to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Navdeep Saini!! What's happened here? Saini is lying on the field and the initial impression was that he might have missed the catch. But nope. It's a spectacular take from Saini. Was a flat hit from Kishan, shuffling across and heaving with all the power he could muster. Saini had some ground to cover and did so to take a wonderful low catch. However, he also landed by bumping his head and that's why he was lying without much reaction for a while. Must have hurt for sure. It's a huge breakthrough though, Rajasthan have some breathing space as the dangerous Kishan departs. Ishan Kishan c Navdeep Saini b Boult 54(43) [4s-5 6s-1]
